\f0\i \cf0 \'93
\i0 Whattaya say, Fred? Stash it for a couple of decades or?\'94
\f1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\fi360\sl400

\f0 \cf0 Fred burst out laughing.
\f1 \

\f0 \'93You\'92re right, \'94 Tom said and took a big gulp which attracted considerable attention from the other inhabitants of the long, cramped alley.
\f1 \

\f0 Fred scrambled up and moved over to Tom\'92s side\'97plopping down on a stack of boxes against the wall.
\f1 \

\f0 \'93Hey, mind the bed, yeh? Couple o' youngsters dropped this off this mornin\'92.\'94
\f1 \

\f0 \'93Awful nice of them. What\'92d you do to deserve that?\'94
\f1 \

\f0 \'93Haven\'92t the foggiest. I asked them too, you know. Said I\'92d figure, or somesuch nonsense.\'94 Tom was starting to feel pretty relaxed. The bite of the cold faded and he felt like the world was falling into a dream. He shuddered for a bit and blinked a few times, exhaling quickly.
\f1 \

\f0 \'93Woo, this stuff must be pretty strong!\'94
\f1 \

\f0 \'93Yeh?\'94 Fred asked, and stretched out his hand. \'93Lemme try it. I bet I can handle it better than you could any day.\'94
\f1 \

\f0 \'93Not a chance.\'94
\f1 \

\f0 Tom twisted the cap on the bottle and lifted it, ready to hand it to Fred. Instead he grabbed it with both hands, raised it as high as he could and brought it down harder than he\'92d imagined possible, hitting Fred square across the face; knocking him to the floor face-down. He didn\'92t move for a few seconds. Surprised that he\'92d done this at all, Tom was suddenly more awake than he\'92d ever been in his life.
\f1 \

\f0 Before he had the chance to think about what was happening, he raised the bottle once more and brought it down again on Fred\'92s head. It shattered, and the liquid spread across the now bloody face in front of him. Terror gripped him as he struggled to speak, to act; to stop.
\f1 \

\f0 Again the bottle impacted his old friend, cutting deep into his skin. Blood covered everything around them; the bottle slipping in his red hands, his shirt stained. It ran across the pavement, collecting into pools at an eerie, slow pace, flowing towards the nearest drain. Tom now hardly recognized his friend, as he kept stabbing him over, and over, and over again.
\f1 \

\f0 \'93Oh my god, somebody call 911!\'94
\f1 \

\f0 The voice came from the street, where people had stopped in shock at the horror of what they were witnessing. A river of tears flowed from Tom\'92s face, mixing with the blood and the booze to form a terrible, bubbling mess. When he finally stopped, he raised his head towards the street to find an officer holding a gun with outstretched, shaking arms. He wanted to scream\'97to yell for help\'97but no matter how he tried to move his body wouldn\'92t budge. As his crying intensified, his body involuntarily started to heave.
\f1 \

\f0 \'93Put the bottle down, and lay face down on the ground!\'94 The officer yelled with a tremble in his voice. Tom\'97his mind momentarily cleared by the adrenaline released by having a gun pointed at him\'97felt for the poor man. He realized the tragedy of what was about to happen, as he relinquished his will to fight. He hoped his forgetfulness would serve him well, at least once more.
\f1 \

\f0 He rose, faced towards the trembling figure and raised the bottle.
\f1 \

\f0 \'93Drop the bottle, sir!\'94
\f1 \

\f0 He stepped forward.
\f1 \

\f0 \'93Stop! Please!\'94
\f1 \

\f0 He stepped forward.
